        "col1_Select the processes that reflect your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "Climate-related issues are considered by the government when undertaking budgeting and/or major capital expenditures",
        "col2_Provide further details on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future by 2070) is prepared through intense stakeholder consultation and launched by the city in June 2023. This action plan includes GPC compliant GHG emissions inventory, ward and area level vulnerability and risk assessment, scenario planning based on various National and State Government targets. City is considering sector wise climate change mitigation and adaptation interventions/ actions/ projects during Annual Municipal Budget Planning every year, which is being approved by city council (Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation General Board). City has constituted Climate Core Team, chaired by Municipal Commissioner and includes head of various departments. Climate Core Team meets every quarter to discuss climate resilient interventions and monitoring implementation status. Information and updates from Climate Core Team is being used for Annual Municipal Budget planning every year. \\n\\nAhmedabad Municipal Corporation has established a 'Net-zero, Environment and Climate Resilient Cell', chaired by Municipal Commissioner and lead by Deputy Municipal Commissioner. All departmental heads are part of the cell. The Cell is responsible for coordinating climate-related efforts across various departments, institutions, and stakeholders, both internally and externally. Operating under the 'Analyse,\\nAct, and Accelerate' approach, the cell is working towards a sustainable future by conducting research, engaging and collaborating with stakeholders, conducting climate readiness reviews, exploring innovative finance options, and integrating climate actions into regular planning processes amongst others. Additionally, the cell supports all departments in\\nprioritising sectoral climate actions, creating a data bank for data-driven monitoring and\\nevaluation, and promoting liveable and sustainable urban planning practices.\\n\\nPlease refer below sections from Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future).1) Annexure 1.1 Formation of Stakeholder Committee and Climate Core Team and Annexure 1.2 Stakeholder Engagement (Page A3 to A8); 2) Chapter 3 (section 3.1.5, 3.2.7, 3.3.2, 3.4.10, 3.5.6, 3.6.2) for information on sector wise budgetary planning for climate actions in FY 2023-24.\\n\\nPlease refer the AMC notification number 243, dated 15/03/2024 for 'Net-zero, Environment and Climate Resilient Cell'.",
        "col3_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's master/development planning": "Ahmedabad Development Plan for 2031(prepared in 2021) is emphasizing on 1) densification of existing areas for optimum resource utilization, 2) enhance the skyline through additional FSIs in central business districts, 3) densification along transit corridors through transit-oriented zone (200m on both sides of metro and BRTS transit corridor, eastern high-density corridor between Narol-Naroda highway (NH8) and 132 feet road on eastern side of the city), 5) development of growth centres around the city and providing logistic zones etc. This planning will help Ahmedabad to manage future growth, regulate density and organize land use within the urban area, which will not only help to provide effective and efficient urban services but also conserve natural resources, save energy, and mitigate GHG emissions. Ahmedabad Development Plan for 2031 also emphasizes on blue green infrastructure management and planning, including lake development, open/ green space conservation and management. Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation is following Town Planning Scheme (local area planning concept), which is micro level implementation of larger Development Plan. \\n\\nPlease refer below sections from Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future).1) Chapter 2 (Section 2.6 - from page number 19 to 22) for land use and development planning",
        "col4_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's financial planning": "Based on Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future by 2070) and climate related issues, city has proposed various climate resilient interventions, which has increased capital allocation of Annual Municipal Budget (i.e., lake interlinking, replacing old water supply and sewerage network, 7MW of RE plants, developing urban forests to increase in green cover, biomining of legacy waste etc.). By implementing climate resilient interventions (i.e., 21MW of RE installed for municipal facilities, replacement of streetlights with EE LED lights) has reduced the operating costs and increased revenue. Also, city has proposed some of the projects based on PPP model for accessing climate finance (i.e., 2000 TPD waste to energy plant, 500 TPD waste to bio-CNG plant etc.). City is in progress for releasing Green Bonds under Government of India's AMRUT 2.0 Scheme. City is also part of Gujarat Resilient Cities Program (GRCP), where city is receiving INR 30,000 million from the World Bank for climate resilient infrastructure for wastewater sector. Please refer below sections from Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future).1) Chapter 3 (section 3.1.5, 3.2.7, 3.3.2, 3.4.11, 3.5.6, 3.6.2) for information on sector wise budgetary planning for climate actions in FY 2023-24.",
