        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) has planted total around 12 million trees from 2021 till date as a part of 'Mission Million Trees Campaign'. AMC planted 1.16 million trees in 2021, 2.07 million trees in 2022, 2 million trees in 2023, 3 million trees in 2024, and 4 million trees in 2025. AMC has also initiated geo-tagging of the trees. AMC is providing 'Kitchen Garden/ Terrace Garden Training' to community to improve green cover in the city. AMC is also providing 10% rebate in property tax for urban green space related interventions at property level under AMC's Green Yellow Blue (GYB) Scheme. Ahmedabad has also developed Urban Greening Policy Measures to improve and maintain green cover of the city, which is first in India. \\n\\nThe Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards a Net-zero Future by 2070) provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each actions to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See section 8.3). Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has established a 'Net-zero, Environment and Climate Resilient Cell' which is responsible to monitor and track the progress of each climate action. Also, the cell is supporting all departments to prepare an annual/ five year action plans with clear targets in line with the Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards a Net-zero Future by 2070) and preparing climate budget for effective implementation. Monitoring, Reporting and Verification (MRV) format is also prepared and will be followed by the city to monitor annual progress."
