    "q1_3": [
      {
        "disclosure_cycle": "2025 Disclosure Cycle",
        "cdp_requesting_org_number": 779465,
        "requesting_organization": "CDP",
        "disclosing_org_type": "City",
        "cdp_region": "India",
        "discloser_country_or_area": "India",
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.3",
        "question_text": "Provide information on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related risks and opportunities and how these issues have impacted your jurisdiction's planning.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "col1_Select the processes that reflect your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "Climate-related issues are considered by the government when undertaking budgeting and/or major capital expenditures",
        "col2_Provide further details on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "The Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan, developed through extensive stakeholder consultations, was prepared and approved in November 2024 by the General Board of the Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation. This comprehensive plan features a GPC-compliant GHG emissions inventory, ward and area-level vulnerability and risk assessments, and scenario planning aligned with various national and state government targets. Each year, during the Annual Municipal Budget Planning, the city considers sector-specific climate change mitigation and adaptation interventions, actions, and projects, which are then approved by the local government (Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation General Board). This information is subsequently used for the Annual Municipal Budget planning each year. Regular meetings with department heads ensure ongoing discussions on climate resilience interventions and monitoring of implementation progress. The city regularly reports its climate actions and initiatives to the Urban Development and Urban Housing Department, Government of Gujarat. \\n\\nPlease refer below sections from Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan. 1) Chapter 3 (section 3.1.6, 3.2.5, 3.3.2, 3.4.8, 3.5.4, 3.6.2) for information on sector wise budgetary planning for climate actions in FY 2024-25.\\n\\nAlso, the year FY 2025-26 has been designated as the ''Urban Development Year'' by the state government of Gujarat to further accelerate the development in urban areas. Under the Urban Development year, Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation has prepared an action plan for the year which also encompasses the aspects like Climate, Sustainability and Renewable Energy under the Pillar 4: Better Living Conditions (Clean and Green Environment). The actions under the Pillar 4 are being regularly monitored by the Urban Development Department, Government of Gujarat. ",
        "col3_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's master/development planning": "Bhavnagar Revised Draft Development Plan for 2041 is emphasizing on 1) Improving land use efficinecy, 2) Developing new areas through TP schemes, 3) Densification along transit corridors, 4) Integrated development of BMC and BADA areas 5) Improving quality of life with adequate infrastructure, 6) Conserving and strengthening green and blue areas, 7) Preservation of heritage buildings, 8) Slum rehabilitation and upgradation, 10) Conservation of salt pans and mud flats and CRZ. This planning will help Bhavnagar to manage future growth, regulate density and organize land use within the urban area, which will not only help to provide effective and efficient urban services but also conserve natural resources, save energy, and mitigate GHG emissions. The Development Plan also emphasizes on blue green infrastructure management and planning, including lake development, open/ green space conservation and management and conserving the ecologically sensitive mud flats and salt pans in and around the city, which are home to various species of birds animals and insects. Like other cities of Gujarat, Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation is following Town Planning Scheme (local area planning concept), which is micro level implementation of larger Development Plan. Under each TP scheme 5% area is reserved for green spaces and 1% is reserved for urban forests. \\n\\nPlease refer below sections from Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan. 1) Chapter 2 (Section 2.6 - from page number 30 to 32) for land use and development planning",
        "col4_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's financial planning": "Based on the Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan and related climate issues, the city has proposed various climate-resilient interventions, which have increased the capital allocation of the Annual Municipal Budget. These interventions include (from the Budget of FY 2025-26, in progress and proposed projects):\\n- Replacing the old water supply and sewerage network\\n- Adding 4 new water treatment plants (90 MLD) at the cost of INR 550 million \\n- Groundwater recharging by involving citizens (70% share of city:30% share of citizens scheme) in private societies for recharging borewells at the cost of INR 30 million; \\n- Conducting topographic survey before laying of key infrastructure lines and roads in New Town Planning Schemes, \\n- Developing Community Halls and Knowledge Centers with Green Building concept to reduce energy consumption and increase energy efficiency\\n- Construction of 100 Bus Stops and operationalizing E-Bus transport system at the cost of INR 100 million\\n- Development of Miyawaki based Urban Forests at various places at the cost of INR 15 million\\n- Installing 6.3 MW Wind Power Plant at the cost of INR 670 million. It will generate 17.4 million units and save approximately INR 120 million.\\n- Setting up 50 TPD construction and demolition waste processing plants. \\n- 50 TPD Bio-Methanation Plant at the cost of INR 300 million\\n- 200 TPD Waste to Compost Plant at the cost of INR 720 million\\n- Construction of 200 TPD Refuse Transfer Station in the East Zone of the city\\n- Replacing all 37,991 streetlights with energy-efficient LED lights, has reduced operating costs and increased revenue. \\n\\nFollowing suggestions from the Urban Development and Urban Housing Department, Government of Gujarat, Bhavnagar is also considering listing Green Bonds to raise INR 250 million for 10% funding under AMRUT 2.0 for financing 36 projects based on its climate actions. \\n\\nPlease refer below sections from Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan. 1) Chapter 3 (section 3.1.6, 3.2.5, 3.3.2, 3.4.8, 3.5.4, 3.6.2) for information on sector wise budgetary planning for climate actions in FY 2024-25.",
        "col5_Describe the risks to your jurisdiction related to the transition to a low-carbon economy": "Bhavnagar is progressing steadily toward high urban growth with a sustainable and low-carbon economy. The city has not encountered any significant risks in this transition. However, it faces a shortage of technical expertise required for adopting new climate-friendly technologies and lacks sufficient technical staff to manage its expanding urban needs. Additionally, the city's technical capacity to access climate finance, especially international funding, is limited."
      }
    ],
