        "col6_Processes for monitoring evaluation and updates of plan^": "Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported every 1-3 years|Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place annually or more frequently than annually|Update: Updates to the plan are published every 3-5 years",
        "col7_Plan status/progress towards plan": "Achieved",
        "col8_Funding sources and financial instruments to finance plan": "Private partnerships (e.g., a combination of private investments)|Jurisdiction's own resources|Public-private partnerships|Climate finance (carbon credits)|National funds and programmes|Regional funds and programmes|Private",
        "col9_Communities and organizations engaged": "Trade unions|National government and/or agencies|Business and private sector|Indigenous peoples|Academia|Citizens|Local government (s) and/or agencies|Non-governmental organisations|Vulnerable population groups|State/regional government(s) and/or agencies",
        "col10_Describe if and how climate-related scenarios have informed the plan": "The Gujarat SAPCC (2021) includes climate projections from three RCP scenarios, RCP 2.6, RCP 4.5 and RCP 8.5, which reflect high, medium and low efforts to curb emissions, respectively. These scenarios are modelled for short term (2011 to 2040), midterm (2041 to 2070) and long term (2071 to 2100) periods. Given that the target year for the Climate Resilient City Action Plan for Ahmedabad is 2030, climate scenarios for the short term and midterm are considered for further analysis. ",
        "col11_Primary author(s) of plan^": "Regional / state / provincial government|Dedicated team within jurisdiction|Relevant department within jurisdiction|International organization",
        "col12_Assessment of co-benefits, trade-offs, and synergies of actions included in plan": "Plan assesses synergies of actions|Plan assesses co-benefits of actions",
