    "q11_1": [
      {
        "disclosure_cycle": "2025 Disclosure Cycle",
        "cdp_requesting_org_number": 779465,
        "requesting_organization": "CDP",
        "disclosing_org_type": "City",
        "cdp_region": "India",
        "discloser_country_or_area": "India",
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q11.1",
        "question_text": "Use this field to provide any additional information or context that you feel is relevant to your jurisdiction's response. Please note that this field is optional and is not scored/assessed.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "col1_Further information": "Bhavnagar Climate Resilient City Action Plan (CRCAP) has been prepared using ICLEI South Asia's ClimateResilientCities methodology. For this, ICLEI South Asia provided technical assistance to Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation for preparing the plan in line with the national, state and city government priorities, following GCoM's Common Reporting Framework (CRF). \\n\\nThis action plan includes a detailed urban system gap analysis; climate risk and vulnerability assessment; a Global Protocol for Community-Scale Greenhouse Gas Emission (GPC) complaint GHG emissions inventory (2022-23); future emissions scenario modelling including Business-As-Usual projections (2025, 2027, 2030, 2040, 2050) and GHG emissions reduction scenario (Low Emission Growth Scenario for 2025, 2027, 2030).\\n\\nThe action plan encompasses 17 strategies and 83 actions across eight key urban sectors: 1) built environment and energy, 2) transport, 3) water, 4) wastewater, 5) storm water, 6) solid waste, 7) urban greening and biodiversity, and 8) air quality.\\n\\nBy implementing the measures specified in the Low Emissions Growth Scenario, Bhavnagar is positioned to reduce its GHG emissions by up to 16.3% compared to the business-as-usual (BAU) scenario by 2030.\\n\\nThe approval letter from the Bhavnagar Municipal Corporation's General Board (Council Approval) for the Climate Resilient City Action Plan (CRCAP), in native Gujarati language, has been attached for reference.\\n\\nThe CRCAP was initially approved by the Municipal Commissioner and subsequently forwarded to the Standing Committee of the Municipal Corporation, which granted its approval. Thereafter, the plan was placed before the General Board (Council) of the Corporation, where it received final approval.\\n\\nAccordingly, the Climate Resilient City Action Plan has been formally approved and adopted by the city.",
        "col2_Further attachments": "BMC CRCAP General Board Approval Resolution.pdf"
      }
    ]
