        "col4_Comment": "The Department of Environment has been renamed as Department of Environment and Climate Change at Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC). This step has been taken to institutionalise climate actions in the ULB. This department would serve as a nodal point for any climate-related initiatives and primarily works on MCAP, alongside other related projects and initiatives such as MVA, Women for Climate, Cities4Forests, NCAP and sustainable development projects under the 15th Finance Commission fund. The department will continue to report to AMC City and be headed by the DMC, Environment & Climate Change. This department will be supported by the State Government of Maharashtra, and the Maharashtra Council for Climate Change. Additionally, a group of honorary advisors (which can be expanded as the plan progresses) will support the Department of Environment and Climate Change for the effective implementation of the MCAP."
