        "col6_Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "\u20b9383 Cr allocated for urban greening with 70 ha. new open spaces (Green Shore, Nature Cove, Park Line). ",
        "col7_Comment": "With support of C40, an implementation pathway for addressing heat risks\\nin Buildings Sector in identified hotspots in Mumbai has been developed. The heat resilience pathway for Mumbai's building sector is tracked through indicators such as baseline temperature trends, hotspot mapping using Local Climate Zone (LCZ) and Land Surface Temperature (LST) data, and vulnerability assessments of building typologies. Evidence of implementation includes stakeholder consultations, pilot retrofitting measures like cool roofs and reflective pavements, policy recommendations to integrate heat resilience in DCPR-2034 and ECBC, and quick-win actions such as building material guidelines and worker protection protocols, which are currently under internal review."
