    "q8_1_1": [
      {
        "disclosure_cycle": "2025 Disclosure Cycle",
        "cdp_requesting_org_number": 779465,
        "requesting_organization": "CDP",
        "disclosing_org_type": "City",
        "cdp_region": "India",
        "discloser_country_or_area": "India",
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q8.1.1",
        "question_text": "Report details on the climate action plan or strategy that addresses mitigation, adaptation (resilience), and/or energy-related issues in your jurisdiction.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "col1_Climate action plan type^": "Integrated climate plan (addressing mitigation and adaptation)",
        "col2_Plan attachment^": "Mumbai Climate Action Plan_c.pdf",
        "col3_Name of plan and URL link, if applicable^": "Mumbai Climate Action Plan (MCAP) - \\n\\nhttps://portal.mcgm.gov.in/irj/go/km/docs/documents/Environment/Climate/Mumbai%20Climate%20Action%20Plan.pdf",
        "col4_Confirm attachment/link provided to plan": "The plan has been attached and can be accessed (unrestricted) on the link provided",
        "col5_Boundary of plan relative to jurisdiction boundary": "Same (jurisdiction-wide) - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "col6_Processes for monitoring evaluation and updates of plan^": "Update: Updates to the plan are published every 5+ years|Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place every 3-5 years|Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported every 3-5 years",
        "col7_Plan status/progress towards plan": "Underway - moderate progress made",
        "col8_Funding sources and financial instruments to finance plan": "Jurisdiction's own resources|Public-private partnerships|National funds and programmes",
        "col9_Communities and organizations engaged": "Non-governmental organisations|Academia|Citizens|Business and private sector|State/regional government(s) and/or agencies|Local government (s) and/or agencies",
        "col10_Describe if and how climate-related scenarios have informed the plan": "Pathways scenario exercise was conducted to establish an evidence base that could be used to set emissions reduction targets for Mumbai's energy, transport and waste sectors in line with the fair-share 1.5 degree scenario and identify the strategies to achieve these. In the MCAP, these scenarios have been used to structure the climate action planning analysis, document Mumbai's current strategies, identify new strategies that could be implemented in the near and medium terms and assess the barriers in implementing ambitious action. C40's landmark research 'Deadline 2020' describes the fair-share 1.5 degree warming scenario trajectory of cities, depending on their specific contexts. The scenarios on Business-as-usual, Existing&Planned and Ambitious models are based on the pathways model developed by C40. These have been developed to model a trajectory that could keep emissions within the limits established in the Paris Agreement. The scenarios, were developed over a period of five months, primarily through desk-based research, and provide an evidence-based roadmap to a\\nfair-share 1.5 degree warming scenario for Mumbai. The pathways scenarios were developed in consultation with key city departments and external stakeholders to gain inputs on feasibility and priorities. Most of the data was provided by different agencies with whom BMC coordinated. For example, SWM data was received from the SWM, Water Supply, Gardens and Storm Water Drainage Departments, energy data from DISCOMS within BMC and Mahanagar Gas Limited (MGL), and transport data from fuel companies, MMRDA, BEST, Regional Transport Offices (RTOs) and Western and Central Railways. Gaps in data were filled using secondary sources.",
        "col11_Primary author(s) of plan^": "Regional / state / provincial government|Dedicated team within jurisdiction|Consultant|International organization|Relevant department within jurisdiction",
        "col12_Assessment of co-benefits, trade-offs, and synergies of actions included in plan": "Plan assesses co-benefits of actions",
        "col13_Year of formal approval of plan^": 2022.0,
        "col14_End year of plan": 2050.0,
        "col15_Total cost of implementation of plan (in currency specified in 1.2)": 0.0,
        "col16_Sectors covered by action plan": "Water supply|Forestry|Waste management|Sewerage, wastewater management and remediation activities|Transportation and storage|Construction|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Manufacturing",
        "col17_Please explain": "The Climate Action Plan covers six sectors which are Energy & Buildings, Sustainable Mobility, Sustainable Waste Management, Urban Greening & Biodiversity, Air Quality and Urban Flooding & Water Resource Management. Under each sectors there are sectoral action tracks provided for mitigation and adaptation targets, with budget/funding/tentative cost, timeline and responsible agencies mapped against every action track. \\n\\nThe total cost of implementation of Mumbai Climate Action plan is not yet estimated."
      }
    ],
