        "col4_Action description and web link to further information^^": "At present Mumbai has 28 CAAQMS station to monitor AQI of the city. BMC itself has set up 5 CAAQMS stations with the help of central grant, XVth Finance Commission under National Clean Air Programme. Further, to monitor at hyper-local level, BMC has proposed to set sensor based monitoring network. In phase 1, 75 nos. sensors will be installed and later upscaled to total 250 nos. sensors throughout the city. The data generated from this sensors will be analyzed and interpreted with the use of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning.\\nTo better understand the contributing air pollution sources in the jurisdiction as well as transboundary emission, the emission inventory of all the sources will be updated every six months for next 5 years.\\nThese all data points will be integral part of Early Air Quality Warning System, that is also being proposed.",
        "col5_Sectors adaptation action applies to": "Construction|Human health and social work activities|Information and communication",
        "col6_Select the attributes of resilience this action enhances": "Decision-making capacity|Availability of diverse options",
