        "col3_Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Urban flooding",
        "col4_Action description and web link to further information^^": "Owing to the low per capita green cover of 1.8sq.m vs URDPFI prescribed 10-12 sq.m, and the reduction in the vegetation cover from 46.42% in 1988 to 26.67% in 2018, only 3.7% open space is accessible for the citizens. The MCAP, with WRI as a knowledge partner, has initiated the planting of 3,77,416 trees across 100 locations along with Mithi river restoration under the Cities4forest and C40 Urban Nature's Declaration commitment for its restoration. Mumbai has ensured the construction of 10 feet walls for mangrove protection across 6 locations \u2014 Charkop; Malad; along the Eastern Express Highway, Vikhroli; Colaba; Wadala, Mankhurd.The 'Mangrove Conservation and Livelihood Generation' scheme (2017) has supported indigenous communities through sustainable livelihood activities such as mud crab and oyster farming, fish cage culture, ornamental fish culture and ecotourism initiatives.The city has also conserved the Aarey Forest, a rich and diverse forest which spans over 3,160 acres of land in the heart of urban Mumbai, thereby protecting a deeply rooted rich culture of the 27 living indigenous tribal communities with a total of over 10,000 population living in settlements known as 'padas'.",
