        "col3_Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Dedicated staff for climate resilience and adaptation are limited, and climate responsibilities are spread across multiple departments. This constrains in-house capacity to interpret climate-risk data, integrate adaptation into sector plans and development control, design robust projects, and track implementation. The city therefore relies heavily on external technical support, which can slow down decision-making and mainstreaming of adaptation measures."
