        "col4_Action description and web link to further information^^": "The City began the exercise of rediscovering its lakes under smart city mission with a \u201carea-based development plan\u201d that focused on revitalising and reviving \u201cthe eight-lake network\u201d. This was followed by Coimbatore Municipal Corporation (CMC) initiating the project of developing \u201cEco- restoration Master plan\u201d of 8 lakes and connecting greenway, with an intention to revitalise environmentally sensitive area and introduce sustainable and enhanced public realm around the lake edges. Integrated development of an EIGHT-LAKE NETWORK to restore it to pristine health, reinforce its flood management capacity and create life-spaces (in 925 acres with natural lake-front habitats with recreational, educational and aquatic facilities) including restoration of natural environs, creation of green spaces, and avenues for recreation and social congregation: - Improvements to water quality - by arresting sewage flows (along with localized waste-water treatment)- Effective flood management through restoration of channels/drains and inter- linkages with other lakes and the Noyyal river system - Developing green pathways with urban forestry/landscaping, cycling and walking tracks- Creating nature spaces such as learning centers, viewing galleries and watch towers.- Encouraging recreation through water sports, fountains, sound/light shows etc.- Creation of a 30 km NON MOTORISED TARNSPORT with green pathways and public cycle sharingThe present project of 8 lakes restoration with NMT corridor is one of the projects under SCM. Its total cost is estimated to be INR 456 crores, in which construction costs are estimated to be INR 442 crores and adiminstration and institutional costs INR 14 crores. Operational and maintenance costs are estimated to be INR 22 crores per annum approximately.",
