        "col3_Outline the purpose of this engagement": "The development of this component is required by the national government (e.g., by law, regulation and/or agreement)|To facilitate information sharing across different levels of government|To facilitate the integration of this component into assessments and policy developed across different levels of government|To collect data and/or feedback from other levels of government to inform its development",
        "col4_Comment": "Even though the consumption of different energy forms happens in the city, GHMC doesn't look into the generation supply of the same, which is done by the various other parastatal bodies, such as TGGENCO, TGSDPCL, and TGREDCO, which play a major role in the conversion from the fossil fuel-based energy sources to renewable energy sources. Even if the city sets targets, the implementation entities will be other bodies that work with state governments. Monitoring and recording of the daily weather are being carried out by the IMD and TGSDPS, which again work in coordination with the center and state governments. GHMC is limited to obtaining information from the departments. Forecasting of heat and rainfall is also sourced from IMD by GHMC. The State groundwater department does monitor of the groundwater system, and GHMC doesn't have any role, but the stress on the water supply is directly linked with the excess extraction of groundwater. "
