        "col2_Degree to which this factor challenges/supports the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Challenges: Significantly challenges",
        "col3_Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Hyderabad currently relies on surface water sources located far from the city, and during the summer months, the city faces frequent shortages due to low water levels, resulting in increased extraction of groundwater. With anticipated increasing temperatures, water demand is likely to increase, potentially widening the gap between the supply and demand. In drought years, this could lead to critically limited water availability for basic needs. "
