        "col3_Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "The availability of relevant data to identify or predict the severity of a hazard and to assess the exposure of vulnerable groups relies on the quality of data collected during past disasters. While manual data collection isn't feasible during an event, as human resources primarily focus on relief activities, having resources or monitoring systems in place for data collection isn't adopted as of now."
