        "col7_Please explain": "Junagadh's climate risk and vulnerability assessment highlights the city's exposure to flooding and rainfall variability. Annual rainfall averages between 700-1050 mm, with extreme events such as 2,800 mm recorded in 1983, underscoring the unpredictability of precipitation. In 2022 alone, Junagadh received 1,318.9 mm over 53 rainy days, straining its drainage systems and causing frequent waterlogging. The composite flood risk map shows that 52.2% of the city's area falls under medium risk, while 42% is at high risk, and nearly 1% at very high risk. Critical social infrastructure\u2014including 44 Anganwadi centers and 126 health facilities\u2014are located in these vulnerable zones. Drainage blocks and inadequate stormwater management further intensify flood hazards, making robust flood preparedness, revival of natural water bodies, and improved drainage infrastructure essential for resilience."
