        "col3_Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Junagadh city has experienced significant\\nfluctuations in its green cover over the past two\\ndecades. In 2001, the green cover area constituteda mere 6.52% of the total city area, reflecting limited vegetation and green spaces. A decade later, in 2011, concerted efforts likely led to a substantial increase in green cover, reaching 22.25% of the city's total area. However, this positive trend did not persist, and by 2021, the green cover had sharply declined to 8.735435 square kilometers, representing only 15.107% of the total city area. This marked reduction underscores the urgent need for sustainable urban planning and conservation measures to restore and preserve green spaces in Junagadh."
