        "col3_Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Urban flooding|Increased water demand|Heat stress|Water stress",
        "col4_Action description and web link to further information^^": "Kakinada is strengthening its adaptation capacity by upgrading key components of its water supply system to improve reliability and resilience under climate stress. The city is enhancing its intake, pumping, and storage infrastructure, including ELSRs and distribution networks, to ensure stable supply during periods of extreme heat and variable rainfall. Efforts are underway to replace old pipelines, reduce leakages, and improve service continuity in low-lying and vulnerable wards that frequently face flooding or supply disruptions. KMC is also expanding metering and preparing system-level improvements to reduce losses and improve pressure management. These upgrades will help safeguard water availability, ensure equitable access for vulnerable households, and improve resilience against climate impacts such as rising temperatures, increased demand, and intense rainfall events.",
