        "col3_Action description and web link to further information^^": "Kakinada Municipal Corporation undertook detailed Investment Grade Energy Audits (IGA) for its water pumping stations and municipal buildings to understand energy consumption patterns and identify efficiency opportunities. The audit covered major facilities such as Aratlakatta SS Tank, Victoria Water Works, Sasikanth Nagar Water Works, the KMC Main Office, Smart City Office, and Command & Communication Center. It revealed high energy use in pumping systems, low pump efficiencies, poor power factors, old fans, and lack of roof insulation. Based on this, the audit recommended practical upgrades such as efficient pumps (IE4 motors), VFDs, BLDC fans, roof insulation, solar PV, and APFC systems. Implementing these measures will reduce energy costs, lower GHG emissions, and improve operational reliability across high-demand municipal facilities, strengthening Kakinada's climate mitigation efforts. \\nRefer to https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_NOuqT-uGEbuV1yoHifhSxQnVKU-WpBW/view",
