        "col2_Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Waste: Install anaerobic digestion",
        "col3_Action description and web link to further information^^": "Kakinada city is advancing strong mitigation efforts in the solid waste sector by promoting waste-to-energy solutions that reduce methane emissions and support circular waste management. As part of this strategy, the city commissioned a 40 TPD bio-methanation plant in 2025, enabling scientific processing of a significant portion of wet waste and reducing the dependency on open dumping. The plant converts segregated biodegradable waste into biogas and slurry, supporting low-carbon energy use and reducing landfill-related emissions. This project is implemented through a Public-Private Partnership (PPP) model, allowing the city to leverage private sector expertise, operational capability, and long-term investment. These efforts are complemented by state-level support under Swachh Bharat Mission and solid waste management guidelines. his mitigation action directly contributes to reducing methane emissions, lowering the volume of waste reaching dumpsites, and increasing renewable energy generation from organic waste.",
