        "question_text": "Use this field to provide any additional information or context that you feel is relevant to your jurisdiction's response. Please note that this field is optional and is not scored/assessed.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "col1_Further information": "Under the CITIIS 2.0 programme, and as directed by the Government of Andhra Pradesh, Kakinada Municipal Corporation will set up a dedicated Climate Change Cell to lead and coordinate climate action in the city. CITIIS 2.0, led by the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs, requires States to establish State Climate Centres for Cities (S-C3), which will then guide the creation of climate cells in cities.\\nThe Government of India has allocated INR 264 crore to strengthen climate governance across the country, of which INR 23 crore has been given to Andhra Pradesh. Swachh Andhra Corporation will oversee and support the formation and functioning of these climate cells. These Climate Change Cells will help cities to plan and implement climate-resilient projects, address local vulnerabilities, and monitor progress using the ClimateSmart Cities Assessment Framework (CSCAF). This will help the city take more effective, data-driven climate action."
