        "col1_Further information": "The 'Rajkot Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Net-zero CRCAP)' has been prepared using\\nICLEI's Net-zero ClimateResilientCities Action Planning methodology. This methodology provides a step-by-step guidance, supported by a range of tools, for developing a Net-zero CRCAP that addresses both climate change adaptation and mitigation.\\nThe plan includes a comprehensive assessment of the urban systems gap analysis, climate\\nrisk and vulnerability assessment, energy profile and GHG emissions inventory, projections\\nincluding scenario planning for future GHG emission reductions through Progressive Action\\nScenario and Net-zero Pathway, and identification of sectoral goals and target setting along\\nwith detailing of the potential adaptation and mitigation strategies and actions. This plan will\\nguide Rajkot in integrating climate actions into regular planning process, outlining necessary\\ninstitutional mechanisms, technical capabilities, and communication channels to effectively\\ncombat climate change.",
