        "col3_Sectors most exposed^": "Water supply|Mining and quarrying|Arts, entertainment and recreation|Administrative and support service activities|Human health and social work activities|Real estate activities|Fishing|Accommodation and food service activities|Education|Other: Tourism (Udaipur is one the most popular tourism hubs in India)",
        "col4_Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "For the past few years, the city has been grappling with issues stemming from extreme temperatures and recurring heatwaves during the summer season. These challenges have resulted in increased water demand, health problems, and hazardous conditions in open dumpsites. Moreover, alterations in precipitation patterns have led to irregular monsoons, resulting in reduced water availability for drinking, agriculture, and other crucial needs. The extreme heat poses significant health risks and strains the energy demand, particularly affecting vulnerable populations like the elderly and young children. Additionally, intensified rainfall events have raised concerns about flooding, leading to damages in infrastructure and settlements, particularly impacting the poor and low-income groups. Furthermore, the combination of extreme heat and water scarcity has also caused shifts in tourism patterns and negatively impacted the local economy.",
