        "col4_Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "Urban flooding in Udaipur poses significant challenges for vulnerable populations. As a rapidly growing urban area with inadequate drainage systems, flooding can have devastating impacts on communities in low-lying areas and informal settlements. Vulnerable groups, such as children, the elderly, and those with limited resources, are particularly at risk. Flooded roads and damaged infrastructure disrupt access to essential services like healthcare and education. Contaminated floodwater increases the threat of waterborne diseases, while livelihood disruptions lead to income loss and food insecurity. Displacement and homelessness exacerbate the hardships faced by vulnerable communities. ",
