    "q1_3": [
      {
        "disclosure_cycle": "2025 Disclosure Cycle",
        "cdp_requesting_org_number": 779465,
        "requesting_organization": "CDP",
        "disclosing_org_type": "City",
        "cdp_region": "India",
        "discloser_country_or_area": "India",
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.3",
        "question_text": "Provide information on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related risks and opportunities and how these issues have impacted your jurisdiction's planning.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "col1_Select the processes that reflect your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "Climate-related issues are considered by the government when undertaking budgeting and/or major capital expenditures",
        "col2_Provide further details on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "The city developed a Climate Resilient City Action Plan (CRCAP), which forecasts future emissions as well as the necessary adaptation and mitigation measures to lessen their effect. The report includes a list of the projects. The city evaluates the list of projects each year and allocates funding for some of them. Once funds have been allocated, their execution is supervised. Every year, the same steps are taken before the financial year budget is finalized",
        "col3_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's master/development planning": " The Planning Cell of VMC has initiated various conservation practices of existing water bodies, such as beautification, gardening, and tree plantation around the water bodies. The current tree cover in Vadodara is approximately 33.60 sqkm, extending to about 15% of the city area. Compared to 9 sq. m per person green cover as per WHO guideline, the green cover in Vadodara is 13.79 sqm per person (2021), which is commendable. VMC has developed 70 Miyawaki technique based urban forests, spread in a total of 1,33,759 sqm area. Additionally, there are 115 parks and gardens owned and managed by VMC. ",
        "col4_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's financial planning": "Vadodara's Climate Resilient City Action Plan aims for a Net Zero Future by 2070, leading to increased capital allocations in the municipal budget and the implementation of various climate actions. These efforts earned the city a 4-star rating from MoHUA under the CSCAF 2.0. Key initiatives include a 350 TPD wet waste to biogas plant, a 1,000 TPD waste-to-energy plant, a 300 TPD C&D waste facility, a 50 TPD plastic waste facility, and the management of 2,500 MT/day legacy waste with private sector support. The city recycles over 100 MLD wastewater, reused by industries, and raised INR 1,000 million through Municipal Green Bonds for wastewater management. Vadodara has replaced all conventional streetlights with LEDs and is upgrading pumping machinery with energy-efficient alternatives. Solar projects include a 10MW canal-top solar PV and over 2MW of grid-connected solar PV installations, with an additional 1.5MW proposed. The Efficient Electrical Energy Cell (EEEC) monitors energy savings, while plans to introduce 200 electric buses and 24 public EV charging stations under a PPP model are underway.",
        "col5_Describe the risks to your jurisdiction related to the transition to a low-carbon economy": "Vadodara is on track for its transition to a low carbon economy. City has not faced any risks in moving forward with this transition. Technical capacity of the city is limited for accessing climate finance, particularly for tapping international finance."
      }
    ],
