        "row_name": "Response",
        "col1_Does the jurisdiction assess the wider opportunities/benefits of climate action?": "Yes, wider opportunities/benefits are assessed for all climate actions",
        "col2_Outline how your jurisdiction assesses the impact of these wider opportunities/benefits": "Wider opportunities/benefits are qualitatively assessed|Wider opportunities/benefits are quantitatively assessed|Wider opportunities/benefits are considered at the action planning stage",
        "col3_Describe the wider opportunities/benefits of climate action the jurisdiction has identified": "Climate Actions proposed under Climate Resilient City Action Plan includes opportunities, social and environmental benefits. The proposed actions will create an estimated 1,45,073 green jobs from Implementation of renewable energy measures (solar and wind power) in buildings, municipal infrastructure, and electric buses. The proposed actions also quantified total vulnerable people (including elderly people, children, women, people with special needs, slums, vendors etc.) benefited due to proposed actions. Please refer below sections from Vadodara Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future). Chapter 8 (From Section 8.3.1.1 to 8.3.8.1) for information on sector wise climate actions and benefits/co-benefits.",
        "col4_Outline if and how your jurisdiction ensures the equitable distribution of climate action opportunities/benefits": "Yes, the jurisdiction is engaging with frontline communities most impacted by climate change|Yes, the jurisdiction undertakes wider benefits and/or equity assessments for its climate actions|Yes, the jurisdiction is collecting disaggregated or spatial data to inform the design and/or monitor the implementation of climate actions",
        "col5_Outline how your jurisdiction quantifies the equitable and inclusive distribution of climate action": "The vulnerability and risk assessment carried out as part of Vadodara Climate Resilient City Action Plan identified and assessed people at risk due to the increased temperature or heat risk (high-surface temperature, (LST hotspot)), urban flooding, and air pollution. The climate action planning process considers vulnerable population by age, by gender, by levels of income, and people with special needs. The estimated climate actions in numbers for total people who would benefit from the proposed actions include the number of vulnerable people in the population: elderly, children, women, people with special needs, slums, vendors, etc. Please refer below sections from Ahmedabad Climate Resilient City Action Plan (Towards A Net Zero Future). 1) Chapter 4 (Section 5.3) for information on risk and vulnerability analysis. 2) Chapter 8 (From Section 8.3.1.1 to 8.3.8.1) for information on sector wise climate actions and benefits/co-benefits.",
