        "col4_Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "City has collaborated with various private player for effective solid waste treatment based on public private partnership (PPP). 1) 5 TPD waste to bio methanation plant, this biogas treatment plant is developed under the Build-Own-Operate-Transfer (BOOT) 2) 300 TPD C&D waste processing facilities on Build Own Operate and Transfer (BOOT) model, Land is allocated by VMC for a period of 25 years. The agency has proposed to share 2.5% of the total profit generated from the sale of recyclable products with VMC. Additionally, it is proposed to reuse these recyclable products for various purposes by VMC. 3) 50 TPD plastic waste processing at Atladara, VMC installed polyethylene terephthalate (PET) bottle crushing machines at three locations (2 at railway station and 1 at bus station), in collaboration with an NGO and ONGC-Vadodara in 2018. Cumulative capacity of these machines is 90 to 120 bottles per hour for converting plastic waste to flakes. 4) 350 TPD waste to bio-CNG plant is proposed on PPP model 5) 1000 TPD waste to energy plant is proposed on PPP model at Makarpura, which will generate 14.9 MW RE. ",
        "col5_Other entities collaborated with": "Industry trade group|Other: Private Players"
