        "col1_Select a reference ID for the goal": "Adaptation goal 2",
        "col2_Adaptation goal^": "To become a water-resilient city by enhancing the local water resources and water infrastructure",
        "col3_Climate hazards that goal addresses^": "Heavy precipitation|Biodiversity loss|Soil degradation/erosion|Increased water demand|Infectious disease|Urban flooding|River flooding|Water stress|Loss of green space/green cover|Other forms of climate-induced landscape shift/degradation",
        "col4_Base year of goal (or year goal was established if no base year)^": 2024.0,
        "col5_Target year of goal^": 2070.0,
        "col6_Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "Below mentioned key performance indicators will\\nbe used by the city to track these goals\\n1)Implementation of local water resource and ground water recharge action plan\\n2)Socially acceptable water meter policy prepared \\n3)Increased length of DI pipeline network\\n4)Increased total number of HHs with 24 x 7 water supply\\n5)Treated wastewater reuse and recycling policy prepared and implemented \\n6)Increased awareness to maximize reuse of treated wastewater and limiting ground water extraction (total number of awareness programs)\\n7)Increased number of industries and commercial consumers reusing treated wastewater\\n8)Capacity of water treatment plant against total water demand (100percentage treated water supply)\\n9)Periodic analysis of performance by using water sensor data from SCADA for efficient water supply (total water supply, water received at end user, pressure monitoring etc.)\\n10)Water supply zones demarcated \\n11)NRW study conducted and being updated every 5 years \\n12)Percentage of water distribution network with sensors installed\\n13)Increased percentage of DI network \\n14)Decreased percentage of NRW\\n16)Number of properties getting tax rebate for getting RWH and ground water recharge systems\\n17)Total CSR/ CER fund received and utilised for this initiative\\n18)Increased number of RWH structures implemented along with sensors linked with ICCC to know amount of water harvested\\n19)Increased number of water ATMs provided in slum areas\\n20)Total CSR/ CER fund received and utilised for this initiative\\n21)Percentage of survey and mapping completed compared to the total area of interest.\\n22)Number of stream orders and bankside constraints identified through watershed analysis.\\n23)Official adoption and integration of river-centric urban planning guidelines into municipal regulations.\\n24)Number and type of flood control structures implemented.\\n25)Percentage of sewage outlets diverted to sewage treatment plants and frequency of riverbed and natural drains are cleaned per year\\n26)Percentage of planned riverfront development projects completed\\n27)Number of riparian species identified and planted along the riverbanks.\\n28)Change in biodiversity index within the micro-ecosystem habitat area\\n29)Establishment of a designated crocodile habitat.\\n30)Number of lakes rejuvenated per year (type of interventions implemented)\\n31)Increased number of floating/ constructed wetlands\\n32)Improved quality of water in lakes\\n",
        "col7_Comment": " \\nIt is proposed to achieve this goal by implementing below mentioned strategy\\n\\nStrategy 1: Robust planning and policy frameworks to priorities water resilience.\\nStrategy 2: Develop a comprehensive water management system providing efficient supply and equitable access to quality water.\\nStrategy 3: Protect, rejuvenate, and revitalize local water resources\\n\\n\\n\\nRefer 8.3.3.1 of Vadodara Climate Resilient City Action Plan - Towards A Net Zero Future by 2070."
