        "col15_Is this target publicly available?": "No",
        "col16_Progress made towards target": "The current tree cover in Vadodara is approximately 33.60 sqkm, extending to about 15% of the city area. Compared to 9 sq. m per person green cover as per WHO guideline, the green cover in Vadodara is 13.79 sqm per person (2021), which is commendable. VMC has developed 70 Miyawaki technique based urban forests, spread in a total of 1,33,759 sqm area. Additionally, there are 115 parks and gardens owned and managed by VMC. VMC has cleared legacy waste from Vadsar dumpsite and has developed an urban forest with more than \\n8,000 trees of 100 native species spread in an area of 30,000 sqm area. VMC has planted more than 2 million trees since 2020-21 as a part of VMC's 'Mission Million Trees' initiative. The city has also geo-tagged trees majorly in Sayaji Baug57 and linked with VMC's 'My Vadodara' application for information and awareness. Initiatives by VMC to expand the urban \\ngreen cover will help address urban heat island \\nimpact while delivering co-benefits"
