    "q1_3": [
      {
        "disclosure_cycle": "2025 Disclosure Cycle",
        "cdp_requesting_org_number": 779465,
        "requesting_organization": "CDP",
        "disclosing_org_type": "City",
        "cdp_region": "India",
        "discloser_country_or_area": "India",
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.3",
        "question_text": "Provide information on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related risks and opportunities and how these issues have impacted your jurisdiction's planning.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "col1_Select the processes that reflect your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "Other processes related to the oversight of climate-related issues: Adopting department wise activities for oversighting the climate related issues with the ULB",
        "col2_Provide further details on your jurisdiction's oversight of climate-related issues": "The Vijayawada Climate Resilient City Action Plan (CRCAP) 2047 is prepared through joint stakeholder consultation involving various departments that are implementing entities in the action plan. This action plan includes a GPC-compliant GHG emissions inventory, ward and area-level vulnerability and risk assessment, and scenario planning based on various National and State Government targets. The city has established a Climate Core Team chaired by the Municipal Commissioner and comprising heads of various departments. In addition, a Stakeholder Committee has been formed to review the CRCAP's strategies and sector-specific actions, and to prioritize projects through a participatory approach aimed at achieving net-zero emissions by 2047 through the adoption of sustainable energy and innovative solutions in city infrastructure and municipal service delivery.\\n\\nVijayawada is actively working on the National Clean Air Program, which aims to reduce air pollution through improved monitoring and control of pollutants, Swachh Bharat Mission, which focuses on solid waste management and AMRUT mission to achieve 100% coverage of water supply, sewerage, stormwater and solid waste services.\\n\\nPlease refer to the sections below from the Vijayawada CRCAP 2047.1) Annexure A Climate Core Team and Stakeholder Committee 2) Chapter 4 for information on sector-wise\\tbudget allocation for the proposed Initiatives and projects by Vijayawada city.",
        "col3_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's master/development planning": "Vijayawada Climate Resilient City Action Plan includes the evaluation of current vulnerabilities, anticipating future climate impacts, and taking proactive steps to mitigate the effects of climate change on urban infrastructure and services. There is no mention of climate change adaptation and mitigation strategies formulated in the Vijayawada zonal development plan.\\n\\nAndhra Pradesh Capital Region Development Authority (APCRDA) has prepared a Perspective Plan for 2050, which includes various urban development strategies such as efficient resource management, green infrastructure, jobs and homes for all, preserve identity and heritage. ",
        "col4_Describe how climate-related issues have impacted your jurisdiction's financial planning": "Vijayawada Municipal Corporation does not have specific budget allocations dedicated solely to climate change mitigation or adaptation in its financial planning. However, provisions for such allocations are expected to be considered during future financial planning, basis the upcoming Climate Resilient Action Plan 2047. Recent flooding caused by the overflow of the Budameru rivulet has severely affected the ULB's financial stability. Extensive emergency response operations\u2014including rescue efforts, temporary shelters, and medical assistance\u2014have substantially increased operational expenditures. Simultaneously, infrastructure damage and disruptions to economic activities have reduced tax revenues. A significant share of capital spending has been redirected toward the repair and reconstruction of damaged infrastructure. The government has conducted loss and damage assessments and provided relief support to affected individuals and communities. To enhance resilience, the ULB has initiated several climate adaptation measures, including the removal of encroachments along the Budameru rivulet, embankment strengthening, installation of real-time water flow sensors, desilting operations, and the enhancement of early warning systems.",
        "col5_Describe the risks to your jurisdiction related to the transition to a low-carbon economy": "Vijayawada will be on track to transition to a low-carbon economy following the implementation of the Climate Resilient City Action Plan, which requires coordinated efforts from all stakeholders, particularly the DISCOMs, APSRTC, and the private concessionaire. However, the city's technical capacity to access climate finance, particularly international finance, is limited. Though VMC has advanced in adopting several technological solutions across its infrastructure and service delivery, the institutional capacity to operate and maintain these interventions remains challenging. "
      }
    ],
