        "col3_Sectors most exposed^": "Construction|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Water supply|Waste management|Transportation and storage",
        "col4_Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "Vijayawada's terrain consists of rocky hills and extensive plains, with landslides occurring mainly due to prolonged rainfall and destabilizing construction activities on hill slopes. Population growth has driven unauthorized settlements into these hazard-prone foothill areas, intensifying vulnerability. UNDP studies show that 2% of the city falls under high landslide susceptibility and 3% under medium, with select pockets exposed to landslide hazards. Around 25% of the total population (0.29 million people) and 30% of slum residents (~0.09 million people) are at risk, as 15 city wards are prone to landslides.\\n\\nLandslides disrupt urban infrastructure and services by damaging water and wastewater pipelines, contaminating water sources, blocking drainage, and blocking transportation networks. Slums in the foothills are particularly affected, with casualties and property damage recorded; mitigation efforts, such as relocation and improved rainfall and water-level monitoring, are essential to reduce risk.\\n\\nRefer to Section 5.3.3 in the attached Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan. ",
