        "col3_Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Between 2017 and 2022, Vijayawada Municipal Corporation (VMC) saw its built-up area expand by 4.7%, primarily in the newly incorporated northern wards. This growth followed the city's Zonal Development Plan but came at the cost of significant loss of vegetation\u201421.6% reduction, equal to 1.96 sq. km. of greenery\u2014mostly in the same wards experiencing rapid development.\\n\\nThe increase in concrete surfaces and decrease in green cover has contributed to a more pronounced urban heat island effect, as well as reduced natural infiltration and aquifer recharge, increasing runoff and flood risks during heavy rainfall. Land Surface Temperature analysis reveals a steady rise in both mean maximum and minimum temperatures, with built-up zones showing the highest warming, particularly intensifying the Surface Urban Heat Island phenomenon during winter.\\n\\nRefer to Section 3.9 in the attached Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan. "
