        "col5_Target year of goal^": 2047.0,
        "col6_Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "The city will use the key performance indicators mentioned below to track this goal. Please refer to section 9.3 of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan, named 'Monitoring & Tracking Progress' on page nos. 276 & 277.\\n\\nKPIs for a few actions are provided below. for a detailed list of KPIs, please refer to Annexure L of the Annexures of the Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan from page no. 84 to 87 to track the implementation of the water supply resilience goal.\\n\\n\u2022 Completion and adoption of the water resource management plan \\n\u2022 Number of groundwater monitoring wells installed\\n\u2022 Percentage of extraction points equipped with digital meters \\n\u2022 Proportion of groundwater and surface water in total water consumption\\n\u2022 Volume of water abstracted from groundwater\\n\u2022 Groundwater consumption per Household\\n\u2022 Number of borewells \\n\u2022 Level of groundwater\\n\u2022 Number of Rain Water Harvesting (RWH) systems installed over a specific period, typically monthly or annually\\n\u2022 Number of residential, commercial, municipal and industrial buildings with rainwater harvesting systems\\n\u2022 Increase in number of residential, commercial and industrial units using treated wastewater and rainwater\\n\u2022 Percentage of the city covered by the 24x7 water supply system \\n\u2022 Increase in percentage of HHs with 24 x 7 water supply \\n\u2022 Number of District Metering Areas established and operational \\n\u2022 Average hours of continuous water supply per day \\n\u2022 Percentage of operational costs recovered through water tariffs and billing\\n\u2022 Percentage of water samples meeting safety and quality standards\\n\u2022 Percentage of water connections equipped with smart meters ",
        "col7_Comment": "It is proposed to achieve this goal by implementing the following strategies.\\n \\nStrategy 1: Effective water resource management including restoration of natural water sources Strategy 2: Efficient, optimum and equitable access to safe water for all\\nStrategy 3: Reduction of non-revenue water \\n\\nRefer to section 7.3.3 (page no. 192 to 198) of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan. "
