        "col3_Climate hazards that goal addresses^": "Urban flooding|River flooding|Other: Health hazards|Extreme heat|Loss of green space/green cover|Biodiversity loss|Heavy precipitation|Heat stress",
        "col4_Base year of goal (or year goal was established if no base year)^": 2025.0,
        "col5_Target year of goal^": 2047.0,
        "col6_Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "The city will use the key performance indicators mentioned below to track this goal. Please refer to section 9.3 of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan, named 'Monitoring & Tracking Progress' on page nos. 276 & 277.\\n\\nKPIs for a few actions are provided below. For a detailed list of KPIs, please refer to Annexure L of the Annexures of the Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan in pages 90 & 91 to track the implementation of the stormwater management goal.\\n\\n\u2022 Percentage of encroached areas identified and cleared along nalas and canals\\n\u2022 Total area of rehabilitated land\\n\u2022 Increase in water flow capacity \\n\u2022 Volume of waste removed from nalas, canals, and other water bodies (in tons)\\n\u2022 Percentage reduction in waste accumulation in cleaned areas after interventions\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in stormwater drainage network coverage and installation of pumping stations adhering to the CPHEEO guidelines\\n\u2022 Reduction in flooding incidents post stormwater drainage network upgradation\\n\u2022 Number of flood-prone areas covered by the monitoring sensors and early warning system\\n\u2022 Response time reduction to flood related incidents after early warning alerts\\n\u2022 Number of early warning alerts issued, and corresponding action taken \\n\u2022 Reduction in the number of flooding events in low-lying, flood prone and hill slope encroachment areas \\n\u2022 Decrease in soil erosion rates on hill slopes\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in green cover through terraced landscapes along hill slopes\\n\u2022 Volume of surface runoff captured by bioswales\\n\u2022 Reduction in pollutants after implementation of BGI elements\\n\u2022 Decreased in surface runoff due to increased permeable surfaces\\n\u2022 Number of percolation wells installed\\n\\n",
