        "col6_Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "The city will use the key performance indicators mentioned below to track this goal. Please refer to section 9.3 of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan, named 'Monitoring & Tracking Progress' on page nos. 276 & 277.\\n\\nKPIs for a few actions are provided below. For a detailed list of KPIs, please refer to Annexure L of the Annexures of the Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan in pages 92 & 94 to track the implementation of the solid waste management goal.\\n\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in households and commercial units covered by door-to-door waste collection services\\n\u2022 Increase in number of waste collection vehicles\\n\u2022 Number of waste collection vehicles equipped with GPS tracking \\n\u2022 Percentage reduction in waste collection complaints from residents\\n\u2022 Increase in fuel efficiency of waste collection vehicles\\n\u2022 Number of waste collection routes optimized through route rationalisation\\n\u2022 Measured reduction in vehicle kilo-meters travelled for waste collection \\n\u2022 Total fuel savings resulting from optimized waste collection and transportation\\n\u2022 Percentage reduction in waste left uncollected or dumped illegally \\n\u2022 Cost incurred per ton of waste collected and transported. \\n\u2022 Percentage reduction in waste going to landfill \\n\u2022 Percentage of waste composted\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in the waste processing \\n\u2022 Number of decentralized facilities established and operational \\n\u2022 Total volume of compost or biogas produced \\n\u2022 Total volume of waste recycled and processed as RDF\\n\u2022 Percentage of waste converted to energy \\n\u2022 Total area of dumpsites bioremediated \\n\u2022 Number of training sessions and public awareness campaigns conducted to promote the 3R principles\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in waste segregation at the source\\n\u2022 Percentage increase in community participation in 3R-related programs and initiatives\\n\u2022 Percentage of reduced quantity of waste generated per capita\\n\u2022 Percentage of waste diverted from going in municipal waste streams through recycling and reuse\\n\u2022 Increase in number of recycling facilities to handle increased recycling capacity\\n\u2022 Percentage of households, businesses and industries complying with 3R-related waste regulations\\n\u2022 Number of enforcement actions taken against non-compliance with 3R regulations\\n\u2022 Number of new policies or regulations implemented to enforce 3R principles\\n\u2022 Number of households actively participating in the home composting ",
        "col7_Comment": "It is proposed to achieve this goal by implementing the following strategies.\\n \\nStrategy 1: Minimise solid waste generation and maximise segregation, reuse and processing at\\nsource\\nStrategy 2: Ensure primary and secondary waste collection and transport in segregated and\\nefficient manner and optimise scientific processing and disposal\\n\\nRefer to section 7.3.3 (page no. 218 to 221) of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan. "
