        "col25_Target status and progress made towards target": "Underway - limited progress made",
        "col26_Please explain": "Refer Chapter 7 on Scenario Planning for Future Emissions Reduction (page no. 151 to 170) and Chapter 7 on Vijayawada's Goals and Strategies for Climate Resilience (page no. 173 to 270) of Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan (CRCAP). Vijayawada Net-zero CRCAP charts a pathway to net\u2011zero emissions by 2047, using scenario planning to set short\u2011term (2030), intermediate (2040), and long\u2011term (2047) mitigation targets and to compare a Business\u2011as\u2011Usual baseline with two pathways: a Progressive Action Scenario and a Net Zero Pathway aligned with India's 2070 commitment and Andhra Pradesh state's Swarna Andhra Vision of 2047. The plan prioritizes energy\u2011efficient buildings, expanded renewable energy, sustainable waste and water management, and low\u2011carbon mobility, developed through ICLEI's Net Zero ClimateResilientCITIES methodology, which guides baseline assessment, strategy prioritization, and target\u2011setting. The BAU trajectory reflects future emissions if no additional measures are taken beyond current policies, while the Progressive Action Scenario scales city\u2011level actions consistent with national and state guidance and grounded in local conditions, infrastructure, adoption levels, resources, and capacity. The Net Zero Pathway adds more ambitious measures to close the gap to net zero by 2047, building on higher\u2011order policy targets and requiring deeper shifts in technology, behavior, and systems. BAU estimation follows principles that link emissions to urbanization rates driven by demographic and economic dynamics, and evaluates rapid, moderate, and slow urbanization pathways (per UN urbanization prospects, IPCC\u2011endorsed SSPs, and Global Cities Institute guidance); Vijayawada's Net-zero CRCAP adopts the moderate urbanization scenario based on the comparison and analysis of its historic and future population growth. Implementation will be tracked through key performance indicators; see the Monitoring & Tracking Progress section for details on metrics and governance for transparent progress review."
