        "col16_Progress made towards target": "The green cover in Vijayawada city in 2022 was around 7 sq. km., around ~11% of the total city\\narea. VMC manages 170 parks including Rajiv Gandhi Park, Indrikeeladhri hill, Gandhi hill, K.L. Rao Park, Gunadala hill, Mugalrajpuram hill, Red Circle hill, Dr. B.R.Ambedkar and Raghavaiah Park,\\nMahatma Gandhi Park, G.V.S. Sastry Park, and Bhavani Islands, among others. These parks include the surrounding hills and connect the environmental landscape. Average tree density in Vijayawada is estimated to be 3.6 trees/hectare; 20% of tree canopy density for tree/forest cover in the city extends for at least 1 hectare area.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
