        "col15_Is this target publicly available?": "Other: Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan is attached. The target for this sector is compared with the business-as-usual scenario by 2047. Link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SC8ITuhFl41CndU8e2TYueebcxKJNxPY/view",
        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada currently faces significant water management challenges, marked by a high Non-Revenue Water (NRW) rate of 33%. Only 25% of household service connections are metered, with 861 sensor-based smart meters collecting real-time data on water pressure and leakage. While SCADA has been installed for the city's transmission system, its expansion to the distribution system is limited by funding constraints\u2014despite operationalizing SCADA being essential for accurately identifying and managing NRW. Currently, there are no plans to scale up smart metering or SCADA to the distribution system. In line with best practices seen in cities like Surat, Vijayawada is working towards setting up a dedicated NRW cell. Key actions being considered include upgrading the aging pipeline network, monitoring for illegal connections and theft, introducing SCADA with leak detection throughout the supply chain, deploying smart meters and volumetric tariffs across all customer categories, conducting a comprehensive NRW study, establishing a rapid-response NRW control cell within VMC, and engaging the community to actively monitor and manage the water supply system.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
