        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada currently generates 150 MLD of sewage, with an installed sewage treatment plant (STP) capacity of 130 MLD. Sludge produced during treatment is solar dried and utilized as manure, and treated wastewater achieves an 87% quality compliance rate as per Service Level Benchmarks. To address future needs and regulatory requirements, the city has planned an additional 50 MLD of STP capacity by 2026 and is upgrading existing facilities to meet disposal standards as mandated by the National Green Tribunal. City plans to construct tertiary treatment modules for both existing and upcoming STPs to ensure higher quality compliance and promote greater levels of recycling and reuse. Strengthening and expanding quality monitoring at the discharge points will further enhance environmental outcomes.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
