        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Currently, Vijayawada achieves a 31% reuse rate for treated wastewater. The Vijayawada Municipal Corporation (VMC) is piloting the Safe Reuse of Treated Wastewater (SRTW) initiative at Autonagar Industrial Estate, with plans to further expand the practice. Efforts are ongoing to engage industrial stakeholders and secure their participation. To advance SRTW, the city will assess the full reuse potential and develop a robust framework that mandates the use of tertiary-treated wastewater, limits groundwater extraction, rationalizes water tariffs for industrial and commercial consumers, and raises awareness. Conducting detailed studies and outreach will help maximize safe and sustainable reuse across industries.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
