        "col15_Is this target publicly available?": "Other: Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan is attached. The target for this sector is compared with the business-as-usual scenario by 2047. Link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SC8ITuhFl41CndU8e2TYueebcxKJNxPY/view",
        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada city has currently seven sewage treatment plants (STPs), four utilize anaerobic technology. However, three of these plants\u2014accounting for approximately 62% of the city's installed treatment capacity\u2014do not have methane capture and energy recovery systems in place, resulting in higher greenhouse gas emissions. Only the Ajith Singh Nagar STP channels methane through gas turbines to produce electricity. To address this, the city will expand its sewage treatment capacity using anaerobic systems equipped with methane recovery, promote and optimize decentralized anaerobic wastewater treatment (DeWATS) with gas capture, and retrofit existing anaerobic STPs with effective methane capture and recovery technologies.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
