        "col16_Progress made towards target": "In Vijayawada, the practice of source segregation remains inadequate in several wards, especially in slum areas, and ongoing information, education, and communication (IEC) campaigns require amplification to achieve greater impact. Waste reduction efforts at the source are minimal. According to the AP Building Rule, large properties are mandated to provide on-site wet waste management systems, but implementation is limited. To address these challenges, the city aims to intensify IEC campaigns to promote source segregation and waste reduction, raise community awareness to prevent littering, and enforce penalties for non-compliance through city-level bye-laws. Promotion of home composting will be maximized using subsidized kits and incentives, while strict enforcement of on-site waste treatment for bulk generators will align with SWM Rules, 2016 and AP Building Rules, 2017. Additional measures include piloting litter-free and bin-free wards, introducing drone-based monitoring at vulnerable points, establishing dedicated monitoring cells for bulk waste generators, mapping and auditing treatment capacity, and conducting bi-monthly checks of on-site treatment facilities to ensure sustained compliance and improved waste management practices.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
