        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada currently disposes of 97 tonnes per day (TPD) of waste at its landfill. The city aims to significantly reduce this figure to 40 TPD by increasing the capacity and operational efficiency of waste treatment plants, as well as by reducing waste generation at the source. To achieve this, Vijayawada plans to identify bulk waste generators that lack the potential for on-site treatment and prioritize them for decentralized waste management solutions\u2014either individually or through collective facilities. Efforts will focus on rejuvenating and expanding the capacity of existing treatment plants, ensuring that only the appropriate waste streams are sent for processing, and that inert materials or true processing rejects are the only types disposed at landfill sites. Furthermore, strategic market analysis and transparent agreements on quality and pricing will help guarantee the sale and uptake of end products from waste processing, supporting sustainable waste diversion.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
