        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Currently, Vijayawada treats about 46% of its waste at a waste-to-energy incineration facility. To further reduce greenhouse gas emissions, the city plans to shift waste treatment towards bio-CNG production and composting. This will involve deploying a combination of centralized and decentralized bio-CNG plants, particularly targeting organic waste streams from flower and vegetable markets. The feasibility of off-taking bio-CNG by agencies like VMC, APSRTC, or other relevant entities will be explored. All new technologies will undergo thorough feasibility assessments to ensure the quantity and quality of incoming feedstock support sustainable and effective operation of bio-CNG and composting systems.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
