        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada currently lacks a methane gas capture system at its scientific landfill, resulting in potential greenhouse gas emissions. The city aims to achieve 100% methane capture from landfill gas by 2040 through the establishment of a sanitary landfill designed for the scientific disposal of inert materials and processing rejects. This new landfill will be equipped with advanced gas capture and leachate management systems. To ensure only residual waste reaches the landfill, its commissioning will follow the full deployment of waste processing and treatment infrastructure. Additionally, drone-based surveillance integrated with the city's Command Control Centre will be used to monitor and prevent unauthorized dumping around the bioremediated and sanitary landfill sites.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
