        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada currently operates 6 electric vehicles (EVs) out of a total fleet of 321 solid waste management vehicles. The city is planning to pilot the electrification of its solid waste collection vehicles in 1 to 2 wards, with a long-term goal of gradually transitioning the entire fleet to electric vehicles. To facilitate this shift, the city will evaluate the remaining lifespan of its existing vehicles, assess future electric fleet requirements, and establish charging stations and parking facilities across all waste collection zones. Incentives such as higher tipping fees, exclusive parking spaces, and dedicated loading and unloading areas will be provided to promote the adoption of electric solid waste management vehicles.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
