        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada's public bus system currently operates 746 buses across 221 routes, covering a total route length of 2,65,576 km and serving around 1.5 lakh passengers daily. To address the city's growing mobility needs, the fleet is projected to expand with the addition of 121 new buses by 2030, ramping up to 564 by 2040, and 1,049 by 2047. In pursuit of enhanced public transport, the city will conduct surveys to improve bus usage and passenger comfort, pinpoint areas for new or upgraded bus shelters, and optimize routes to better serve high-demand corridors. New smart bus shelters will be developed, equipped with amenities such as benches, drinking water, phone charging, solar-powered LED lighting, and surveillance systems. Bus stops will be clearly marked with segregated lanes to improve safety. Additionally, the city aims to reintroduce a Bus Rapid Transit System (BRTS) with refreshed branding, free trial runs, targeted social media campaigns, and focus group consultations to understand better and meet community needs.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
