        "col15_Is this target publicly available?": "Other: Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan is attached. The target for this sector is compared with the business-as-usual scenario by 2047. Link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SC8ITuhFl41CndU8e2TYueebcxKJNxPY/view",
        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Currently, Vijayawada has a non-motorized transport (NMT) mode share of 25%, but only 4.3% of its road network is equipped with footpaths, and visible pedestrian crossings are present on just 42% of roads. High pedestrian activity is observed in major junctions such as Ramesh Hospital Junction, Hindu College Junction, Nazz Center, Sitara Junction, KR Market, and Benz Circle. To improve walkability and safety, the city plans to survey and address gaps in existing pedestrian infrastructure\u2014including issues related to encroachment, inadequate footpath width, insufficient street lighting and amenities, and lack of physical segregation from traffic. Efforts will focus on enhancing and expanding footpaths, especially near bus stops and terminals; piloting pedestrianization in high footfall areas; and introducing citywide street design guidelines for pedestrian and NMT-friendly features. Initiatives will prioritize universal accessibility, integration of greenery and street furniture, better lighting, and implementation of protective barriers. Furthermore, a dedicated NMT budget will be established within the city's annual budget to support continuous improvements.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
