        "col15_Is this target publicly available?": "Other: Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan is attached. The target for this sector is compared with the business-as-usual scenario by 2047. Link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SC8ITuhFl41CndU8e2TYueebcxKJNxPY/view",
        "col16_Progress made towards target": "APSRTC currently does not operate any electric buses within Vijayawada. While the Comprehensive Mobility Plan (CMP), 2017 proposed hop-on-hop-off buses for key tourist destinations and minibuses for low-density corridors\u2014both of which present opportunities for electrification\u2014the Vijayawada Municipal Corporation is now targeting a substantial scale-up of electric buses in collaboration with APSRTC, aiming for 350 by 2030, 1,432 by 2040, and 2,482 by 2047. To support this transition, APSRTC and the Vijayawada Municipal Corporation will organize capacity-building workshops for public and private bus operators and drivers, focusing on electric bus operations, maintenance, available subsidies, and reskilling. The city intends to identify the most suitable routes for electrification based on trip lengths and bus range, engage with DISCOMs to assess and fulfill charging infrastructure requirements, and install both fast and slow chargers at all bus depots to enable seamless electric bus deployment.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
