        "col16_Progress made towards target": "The Vijayawada Municipal Corporation (VMC) is actively developing guidelines for constructing sustainably cooled and heat-resilient buildings. The VMC Main Office Building and Council Hall, both equipped with solar rooftops, can serve as pilot projects for green or zero-carbon buildings. To implement these measures, VMC plans to establish an energy efficiency cell responsible for conducting energy audits of municipal facilities such as STPs, water and drainage pumping stations, hospitals, schools, and other offices. The cell will also explore and pilot best practices for energy efficiency in municipal, residential, and commercial buildings while organizing awareness workshops for VMC staff on energy conservation. Key actions include regular energy audits and tailored retrofits for municipal buildings, piloting green building strategies in key facilities using recycled materials and water-saving features, installing cool roofs on all government buildings, mandating the use of LED lights and BLDC fans, and ensuring procurement of only BEE 4- or 5-star rated appliances for heating, cooling, and lighting across all VMC buildings.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109)."
