        "col16_Progress made towards target": "Vijayawada city is committed to increasing the share of renewable energy to power commercial and institutional buildings, with a strategic focus on high-rise commercial structures (G+3 and above), which represent 85% of the city's total commercial footprint. Collaborative efforts will be made with private technology providers to develop an app that enables consumers to apply for and track rooftop solar installations. Vijayawada Municipal Corporation will also publish a comprehensive guidebook covering application steps, financing models, key stakeholders, and available subsidies and schemes for rooftop solar. Awareness around rooftop solar's advantages will be raised through citywide media campaigns, advertisements, and community workshops covering incentives, maintenance, net metering, and various business models. Additional workshops will inform communities about financial opportunities such as the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana and other government or bank-backed loan and subsidy schemes. To further support sector growth and job creation, the city plans to introduce Solar Technician ITI courses in all public colleges.\\n\\nThe Vijayawada Net-zero Climate Resilient City Action Plan Annexure report provides 'Key Performance Indicators' against each action to monitor and evaluate the achievement of proposed targets (See Annexure L, pages 84 to 109). "
