        "question_number": "Q9.2",
        "question_text": "Describe the outcomes of the most significant mitigation actions your jurisdiction is currently undertaking. Note that this can include those in the planning and/or implementation phases.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "col1_Select a reference ID for the action": "Mitigation Action 1",
        "col2_Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Transportation: Electric vehicle charging points and infrastructure",
        "col3_Action description and web link to further information^^": "Vijayawada city is pursuing ambitious mitigation actions in the transportation sector to reduce greenhouse gas emissions and promote sustainable mobility, with a focus on widespread adoption of electric vehicles (EVs) and supporting infrastructure. \\n\\nThe Municipal Corporation (VMC) has issued tenders and identified 60 strategic locations\u2014such as vegetable markets, commercial complexes, VMC circle office, parking spaces, hospitals, police stations, dumping stations, and universities\u2014for the installation of 105 public EV chargers. These locations ensure high accessibility for residents, businesses, and service vehicles, facilitating the transition to electric mobility while reducing air pollution in highly trafficked urban nodes. \\n\\nTo complement these efforts, the city also aims to develop robust guidelines for integrating charging stations into new developments and existing municipal buildings, and will promote renewable energy-powered charging by piloting solar EV charging stations, especially at public transport depots and auto rickshaw stands. \\n\\nThese initiatives are supported by partnership models, such as public-private partnerships (PPPs) with leading energy and mobility companies, incentives under Andhra Pradesh's Electric Mobility Policy, and grants from central schemes such as FAME II and the India E-Mobility Financing Programme.\\n\\nThis mitigation action will increase the penetration of electric vehicles, optimize the use of sustainable energy for mobility, and shift urban transportation towards a low-carbon, resilient future, aligning with Vijayawada's net-zero emission targets for 2047.",
        "col4_Start year of action": 2024.0,
        "col5_Year for which mitigation is expected to last": "End year not known/not applicable",
        "col6_Impact indicators measured^^": "None of the above impacts associated with this action have been measured",
